Cutar HIV: China ta ruwaito karuwar sabbin kamuwa da cutar da kashi 14%
China ta ba da rahoton karuwar kashi 14 cikin 100 na yawan mutanen da ke dauke da cutar HIV ko kuma masu fama da cutar daji.
Hukumar kiwon lafiya ta ce mutane sama da 820,000 ne ke da cutar a ƙasar.
An samu sabbin kamuwa da cutar 40,000 a kwata na biyu na shekarar 2018 kadai.
Yawancin sababbin kamuwa da cuta sun faru ne ta hanyar jima'i, wanda canji ne daga abin da ya kasance.
A baya, cutar HIV ta yaɗu da sauri a wasu yankunan ƙasar Sin ta wurin ba da jini da aka yi wa ƙwayoyin cuta.
A wani taron da aka yi a lardin Yunnan, ma'aikatan kiwon lafiya na ƙasar Sin sun ce, adadin mutanen da suke kamuwa da cutar ta HIV ta wannan hanyar ya ragu zuwa kusan babu.
Amma, adadin waɗanda suke kamuwa da cutar HIV, ko kuma AIDS, ya ƙaru da mutane 100,000 a kowace shekara.
Cutar HIV ta hanyar jima'i babbar matsala ce a cikin al'ummar LGBT na kasar Sin.
An sake yin jima'i a kasar Sin tun 1997, amma har yanzu ana nuna wa LGBT wariya.
Domin dokokin da suka fi na yau da kullum a ƙasar, bincike ya nuna cewa kashi 70 zuwa 90 cikin ɗari na maza da suke yin jima'i da mazaje suna auren mata.
Yawancin cututtuka suna faruwa ne domin rashin kāriya ta jiki a waɗannan ma'aurata.
Tun 2003, gwamnatin kasar Sin ta yi alkawarin samar da magungunan cutar HIV ga kowa a matsayin wani ɓangare na shirin magance matsalar.
